          "notes": "This is a high-quality module with strong narrative framing, conceptual rigor, and excellent progression across four lessons; the opening hospital triage scenario is genuinely compelling and the stakeholder/power analysis in L3 is notably sophisticated for an introductory module. The primary weakness is in lab executability: all four labs depend entirely on an AI tutor chatbot with no fallback instructions, no rubric for self-assessment, no sample outputs, and no indication of how the AI assistant is configured or whether it will be available — if the chatbot fails or underperforms, the learner has nothing to do. Quiz questions are well-constructed, testing judgment rather than recall, and the module successfully installs a durable conceptual framework (governance vs. ethics, gap causes, stakeholder power, urgency convergence) that constitutes a genuine capability delta.",
          "topIssue": "Lab executability is entirely dependent on an undocumented AI chatbot with no fallback scaffolding, no sample responses, no self-assessment rubric, and no structured worksheet alternative — if the chat interface fails or the AI gives poor pedagogical feedback, learners cannot complete the labs meaningfully; each lab needs a minimum viable paper-based or structured template version alongside the chat interface.",
